description: "Labels on this late 18th century map of Southeast Asia describe two indigenous populations—the ‘Kemoy’ of the mountains along the border of Cochin China (Vietnam) and Camboja (Cambodia), and the ‘Biayos’ of central Borneo—as ‘a wild Nation’."
title: "The East India Islands : comprehending the Isles of Sunda, the Moluccas and the Philippine Islands / by Samuel Dunn."
